-- Money Managers Bullish Bets on Robusta Coffee at 2013 Low
-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 2013-05-13T12:05:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-13/money-managers-bullish-bets-on-robusta-coffee-at-2013-low.html
Money managers  reduced bets  on rising
prices of robusta coffee traded in London to the lowest level
this year in the week ended May 7, according to NYSE Liffe, the
derivatives arm of NYSE Euronext.  The net-long position, a wager on a higher market, fell to
2,502 futures and options contracts in the period, the
Commitments of Traders report published on the exchange’s
 website  today showed. That’s down from 5,337 contracts a week
earlier and the smallest net-long position since Dec. 25,
exchange data compiled by Bloomberg showed. The beans used in
instant coffee gained 0.1 percent in the week.  In cocoa, money managers reduced bets on higher prices by
2.1 percent, the data showed. The  net-long position  fell to
42,068 contracts from 42,972 a week earlier. The beans used to
make chocolate gained 1.9 percent in the week.  Managers cut their bullish bets on white, or refined, sugar
to 1,351 futures and options, according to the exchange. That’s
down from 2,842 contracts a week earlier. The sweetener declined
2.2 percent.  In feed wheat, money managers increased their net-short
position to 422 contracts from 420 a week earlier. The grain
fell 1.2 percent in the period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
